"    </em>",
"    spp, stained with hematoxylin and eosin (H&amp;E). Note the thick outer tegument and the loose parenchyma filling the body. Calcareous corpuscles (red arrows), characteristic of the cestodes, can be seen in the parenchyma. Eggs (blue arrows) can also be seen.",
